title: 100 keV deuteron induced reactions on natural lithium

x4freetext: 100 keV deuteron induced reactions on natural lithium

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.80, p.044617 (2009)

x4freetext: Natural lithium of 2.7 mg/cm2 thickness
Si surface-barrier detector (SSB) with
effective area 25 mm2 and thickness 100 mu-m.
The SSB detector was calibrated using 5.48 MeV
alpha-particles emitted by an Am-241 source
Detection of alpha particles
Total uncertainty in cross-section is  14% and
includes statistical and systematic errors.
All following errors are added in quadrature:
Full systematic uncertainty includes:
the target thickness 10%,
the deuteron current 2%,
the distances between the lithium target to the
SSB detector 0.25%,
the solid angle subtended by the detector 1%,
counts due to the contributions from the
electronic and detector dead time 2%,
the energy calibration of the detector 0.5%,
an error of 10% to the cross section also
appears from the analysis and extraction of the peak
sum and uncertainty in estimating the total cross
section from the polynomial.
Data are from author: B.Lalremruata
Entry approved by B.Lalremruata + NDS
compiled by author B.Lalremruata, V.K.Mulik,
and A.B.Pawar
BL: Energy units were corrected: MeV => keV
